<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>howto on technical_</title><link>https://blog.agramakov.me/tags/howto/</link><description>Recent content in howto on technical_</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language/><lastBuildDate>Sun, 08 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.agramakov.me/tags/howto/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Configure Visual Studio toolchain on Eclipse</title><link>https://blog.agramakov.me/posts/2018/07-08-configure-visual-studio-toolchain-on-eclipse/</link><pubDate>Sun, 08 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.agramakov.me/posts/2018/07-08-configure-visual-studio-toolchain-on-eclipse/</guid><description><p>1. Install software:</p><ul><li><p><a href="http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/eclipse-ide-cc-developers/oxygen3a" target="_blank">Eclipse IDE for C/C++ Developers</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/" target="_blank">Visual Studio</a></p></li></ul><p>2.<strong>Open</strong> Eclipse -> Help -> Install New Software&hellip; -></p><p>Work with: <code>http://download.eclipse.org/tools/cdt/releases/9.4/</code> -></p><p>CDT Optional Features -> C/C++ Visual C++ Support 9.4.3.201802261533</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_67.png" alt="screen_eclipse_67.png"/></p><p>-> Next -> Agree -> Install -> Finish -> Restart</p><p>3.<strong>Close</strong> Eclipse</p><p>4.<strong>Open</strong> Developer Command Prompt for VS 2017 and run from it Eclipse (this trick will add all needed VS environment variables to path)</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_cmd_66.png" alt="screen_cmd_66.png"/></p><p>5. Create new C++ project</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_68.png" alt="screen_68.png"/></p><p>6. Open Project Properties</p><p>C/C++ General -> Paths and Symbols -> Includes -> Add&hellip; -></p><blockquote><p><code>${VSINSTALLDIR}/VC/Tools/MSVC/14.11.25503/include</code></p></blockquote><p>+ Add to all configurations</p><p>+ Add to all languages</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_69.png" alt="screen_eclipse_69.png"/></p><p>7. Ok -> Apply and Close -> Yes</p><p>8. Build</p><p>9. Run -> Run configurations</p><ul><li><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_70.png" alt="screen_eclipse_70.png"/></li><li>C/C++ Application -><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_71.png" alt="screen_eclipse_71.png"/></li><li>Run</li></ul><p>10. Done!</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_eclipse_72.png" alt="screen_eclipse_72.png"/></p></description></item><item><title>Install OpenCV for Visual Studio C++ development</title><link>https://blog.agramakov.me/posts/2018/07-06-install-opencv-for-visual-studio-c-development/</link><pubDate>Fri, 06 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.agramakov.me/posts/2018/07-06-install-opencv-for-visual-studio-c-development/</guid><description><p>1. Get software:</p><ul><li><a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/opencvlibrary/files/opencv-win/" target="_blank">OpenCV</a> (for this article writing time 3.4.1 is the last version)</li><li><a href="https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/" target="_blank">Visual Studio</a></li></ul><p>2. Install Visual Studio; Unpack OpenCV somethere and<a href="https://www.rapidee.com/en/about" target="_blank">add enviromental variable</a></p><p><code>OPENCV\_DIR = C:\\opencv-3.4.1-vc14\_vc15\\opencv\\build\\x64\\vc15</code></p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_rapidee_57.png" alt="screen_RapidEE_57.png"/></p><p>3. Create Windows Console Application in Visual Studio</p><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_devenv_58.png" alt="screen_devenv_58.png"/></p><p>4. Add OpenCV to a project property</p><ul><li>Add <code>$(OPENCV_DIR)\..\..\include</code> to C/C++ - General - Additional Include Directories</li></ul><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_devenv_59.png" alt="screen_devenv_59.png"/></p><ul><li>Add <code>$(OPENCV_DIR)\lib</code>  to Linker - General - Additional Library Directories</li></ul><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_devenv_61.png" alt="screen_devenv_61.png"/></p><ul><li>Add <code>opencv_world341.lib</code> and  <code>opencv_world341d.lib</code> to Linker - Input - Additional Dependencies</li></ul><p><img class="img-zoomable" src="screen_devenv_62.png" alt="screen_devenv_62.png"/></p><p>5. Add code (add path to you image at 13-th line):</p><div class="highlight"><div style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"><tr><td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f" id="hl-0-1"><a style="outline:none;text-decoration:none;color:inherit" href="#hl-0-1"> 1</a></span><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f" id="hl-0-2"><a style="outline:none;text-decoration:none;color:inherit" href="#hl-0-2"> 2</a></span><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f" id="hl-0-3"><a style="outline:none;text-decoration:none;color:inherit" href="#hl-0-3"> 3</a></span><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f" id="hl-0-4"><a style="outline:none;text-decoration:none;color:inherit" href="#hl-0-4"> 4</a></span><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f" id="hl-0-5"><a style="outline:none;text-decoration:none;color:inherit" href="#hl-0-5"> 5</a></span><span style=